Title: Soliton S matrices for the critical A_{N-1}^(1) chain
Authors: Anastasia Doikou and Rafael I. Nepomechie
Comments: 12 pages, LaTeX; v2. contains ``Note Added'' and 1 more reference
Report-no: UMTG-219
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Exactly Solvable and Integrable
  Systems
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B462 (1999) 121-131
\\
  We compute by Bethe Ansatz both bulk and boundary hole scattering matrices
for the critical A_{N-1}^(1) quantum spin chain. The bulk S matrix coincides
with the soliton S matrix for the A_{N-1}^(1) Toda field theory with imaginary
coupling. We verify our result for the boundary S matrix using a generalization
of the Ghoshal-Zamolodchikov boundary crossing relation.
